1
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,460
When we were kids,

2
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:27,800
we met each other once.

3
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:36,970
Hurry up!

4
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,830
Hi, do you want to play with us?

5
00:01:01,210 --> 00:01:02,360
Let's go on that one!

6
00:01:02,390 --> 00:01:02,860
Okay.

7
00:01:13,220 --> 00:01:14,730
That was so much fun!

8
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:21,080
Go away!

9
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:44,570
Zhang Junjia!

10
00:01:44,670 --> 00:01:46,270
Time to come home for dinner!

11
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:47,700
Coming!

12
00:01:51,470 --> 00:01:52,840
Aren't you going home?

13
00:01:55,930 --> 00:01:57,820
Where are your mom and dad?

14
00:02:10,690 --> 00:02:11,960
It wasn't an accident.

15
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,800
Instead, it felt more like fate.

16
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,870
Like the ninth fret of a guitar,

17
00:02:20,079 --> 00:02:21,900
where a name hidden deep
in your heart lies—

18
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,430
once it sounds,

19
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:25,610
it can never be denied.

20
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:28,820
I found you.

21
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:23,980
[Smile After Tears]

22
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:29,480
[Fret 9: The Luck of Being Needed by You]

23
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,750
Give me the bag.

24
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:42,550
It's all wet.

25
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,280
Wait a moment.

26
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:08,840
Dry yourself off first,

27
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,760
or you'll catch a cold.

28
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,060
I can do it myself.

29
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:15,850
Just wait one more second.

30
00:04:27,570 --> 00:04:29,070
I've put a clean towel

31
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,360
and some fresh clothes
in the bathroom for you.

32
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,620
Go take a shower first,

33
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:33,990
or you'll catch a cold.

34
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:34,800
Come on.

35
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,560
Come, have a seat.

36
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:21,180
I can do it myself.

37
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:26,410
I made you a cup of ginger tea.

38
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:29,280
Drink it before bed. It'll keep you warm.

39
00:05:30,210 --> 00:05:31,010
Thank you.

40
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,100
Do you

41
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:35,409
live here by yourself?

42
00:05:35,430 --> 00:05:37,760
My parents both work out of town,

43
00:05:38,770 --> 00:05:40,430
so just make yourself at home.

44
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:46,900
I'm going to tidy up the room.

45
00:05:47,610 --> 00:05:48,409
Wait a moment.

46
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:18,430
Well...

47
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:19,790
I've tidied up the room.

48
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:22,000
I'm going to take a shower.

49
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:26,330
Good night.

50
00:06:26,910 --> 00:06:27,580
Good night.

51
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:46,930
Dinner's ready!

52
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:49,970
So both your parents

53
00:06:49,970 --> 00:06:51,470
work away from home?

54
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:53,909
Do you live with your grandma, then?

55
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:57,580
That's great.

56
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:59,350
Since you live nearby,

57
00:06:59,450 --> 00:07:00,780
Junjia will have someone

58
00:07:00,780 --> 00:07:02,110
to play with from now on.

59
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,430
Hey, little guy,

60
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:06,370
what's your name?

61
00:07:07,290 --> 00:07:09,390
Everyone calls me Panda.

62
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:10,440
Panda?

63
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:12,870
That's adorable.

64
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:14,500
Hang on a second.

65
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,430
Here, have some vegetables.

66
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:22,260
Come on, eat a little more.

67
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:25,240
I have a panda too.

68
00:07:25,530 --> 00:07:26,630
This is for you.

69
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:31,900
Really?

70
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:34,220
From now on, we're friends.

71
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:20,750
Morning.

72
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,730
Did you

73
00:08:26,470 --> 00:08:27,700
make all of these?

74
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,080
After my grandma passed away,

75
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,610
I've been living by myself.

76
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:33,539
I make my own meals every day.

77
00:08:36,179 --> 00:08:37,240
Eat while it's hot.

78
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:50,750
Go on, eat.

79
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:03,490
It's so good!

80
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,710
This is really good too.

81
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,270
I'm actually a pretty good cook.

82
00:09:11,270 --> 00:09:12,410
From now on,
if there's anything you want to eat,

83
00:09:12,410 --> 00:09:13,540
I'll make it for you.

84
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,340
Really?

85
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:16,720
Then I want

86
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,420
a lobster feast!

87
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,170
Well...

88
00:09:20,170 --> 00:09:22,030
That might be a little difficult.

89
00:09:47,210 --> 00:09:49,010
Here. I'm returning this to you.

90
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:52,290
I found it for you.

91
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:54,760
But

92
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:56,590
it seems to be broken.

93
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:01,970
I'm sorry.

94
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:05,090
It can't be put back the way it was.

95
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,210
Just like you said,

96
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:10,670
it can never be the way it was.

97
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,340
But

98
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,010
thank you anyway.

99
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,620
Junjia,

100
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:28,490
can you

101
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:30,260
promise me something?

102
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,570
What is it?

103
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:33,960
Don't say "thank you" to me anymore.

104
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,000
Because I don't do these things
for anything else—

105
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,330
as long as you're happy,

106
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:40,930
that's enough for me.

107
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:42,800
I know.

108
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:46,170
As for

109
00:10:46,410 --> 00:10:47,670
what's bothering you,

110
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,540
you can tell me

111
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:51,000
whenever you feel like it.

112
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:52,450
So

113
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,210
stay

114
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,510
as long as you want.

115
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:01,220
Eat up.

116
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:15,250
[I'll be staying at a classmate's place
for a few days.]

117
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,360
Your parents passed away too.

118
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,780
They left you in my care.

119
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,200
Do you think I'm not tired?

120
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,940
Do you think I don't want to let go?

121
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:23,530
[I'll be staying at a classmate's place
for a few days.]

122
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:25,140
[Why bother someone else?]

123
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:26,410
Who's the one

124
00:11:26,490 --> 00:11:27,890
checking in on you, then?

125
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:28,950
A friend.

126
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:29,780
Go away.

127
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:33,350
Are you sure?

128
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:38,690
I saw someone following you

129
00:11:38,690 --> 00:11:40,620
when you came to work the other day.

130
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:45,730
I think you should go

131
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:48,390
get a blessing or something
—cleanse your aura.

132
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:49,660
Xingtian Temple.

133
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:50,340
Xingtian Temple is a good choice.

134
00:11:50,340 --> 00:11:51,740
You're overthinking it.

135
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,170
Go wash the rags.

136
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:00,780
Did you secretly come to watch me at work?

137
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:08,800
[Tea eggs – 9 NT each.]

138
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:04,210
Who would be so bored
as to do something like that?

139
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:20,630
Towel.

140
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,480
Do you want me to grab a towel for you?

141
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:43,290
You were really clueless yesterday.

142
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,810
How could you forget I was home?

143
00:12:44,810 --> 00:12:46,070
Don't even bring it up.

144
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:48,430
It's embarrassing.

145
00:13:11,130 --> 00:13:14,650
[Jiasheng Memorial Building]

146
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,000
Smells so good.

147
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,670
Do you need help?

148
00:13:29,220 --> 00:13:29,940
No need.

149
00:13:29,970 --> 00:13:31,570
Just sit here and wait for me.

150
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:33,810
Here it comes.

151
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:34,940
The last dish—

152
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:36,670
stir-fried loofah with clams.

153
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,400
♪ I wanna hide away in the last century ♪

154
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:42,890
♪ And just let my mind drift for a while ♪

155
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,520
♪ Whatever's happening out there ♪

156
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:48,480
♪ I don't even want to guess ♪

157
00:13:49,190 --> 00:13:52,590
♪ When I'm tired,
I'll pretend I've forgotten ♪

158
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:58,040
♪ And throw all my worries into the sea ♪

159
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,410
♪ I don't have superpowers ♪

160
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:03,450
♪ Even my strength runs out ♪

161
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:12,810
♪ When I'm tired,
I'll pretend I've forgotten ♪

162
00:14:12,830 --> 00:14:13,840
♪ And throw all my worries ♪

163
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:19,020
[Learning Knows No Bounds.
Education Is for All.]

164
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:18,220
I've got an interschool
tournament next week.

165
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:19,550
Will you come and watch?

166
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:20,920
Of course.

167
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,370
Junjia!

168
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:32,260
Junjia!

169
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:35,740
Junjia!

170
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:36,740
Junjia!

171
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,770
What are you doing?

172
00:14:41,210 --> 00:14:41,610
No, no.

173
00:14:41,610 --> 00:14:42,730
Don't tear that down!

174
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:44,180
Get back to class!

175
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:44,790
Sir,

176
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:46,550
could you ask the school

177
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:46,910
No!

178
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:47,580
not to take it down just yet?

179
00:14:47,580 --> 00:14:48,280
Those are the principal's orders.

180
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,210
Go back to class!

181
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:49,750
Hey!

182
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:50,810
Don't tear it down!

183
00:14:52,220 --> 00:14:52,790
Junjia!

184
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:08,900
You may still have some bruising here.

185
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:11,510
It'd be best to get it checked out
at the hospital,

186
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:12,070
okay?

187
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:12,840
Okay.

188
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:16,610
Done.

189
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,080
Thank you, miss.

190
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,010
You're welcome.

191
00:15:19,380 --> 00:15:20,110
I'm sorry.

192
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,920
What are you apologizing for?

193
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,200
If it weren't for me,

194
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,050
you wouldn't have gotten hurt.

195
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,720
It's nothing.

196
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:30,100
I get strains and sprained ankles
all the time

197
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,610
when I play basketball.

198
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:32,690
Besides,

199
00:15:32,990 --> 00:15:34,310
the important thing

200
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:35,990
is that you didn't get hurt.

201
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:40,460
[School Infirmary]

202
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,240
That's mine.

203
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:47,890
You're injured, aren't you?

204
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,040
I'll carry it.

205
00:15:50,130 --> 00:15:50,700
Okay.

206
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:55,770
Are you sure you don't want me

207
00:15:55,770 --> 00:15:57,470
to go to the hospital with you?

208
00:15:58,190 --> 00:15:59,050
No need.

209
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,630
Don't you have work?

210
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,260
But...

211
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:04,590
Are you sure you'll be okay
going by yourself?

212
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:05,790
Really, I'll be fine.

213
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:08,000
Are you sure?

214
00:16:09,150 --> 00:16:09,820
I'm sure.

215
00:16:10,730 --> 00:16:12,660
If you're still worried,

216
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,040
I can send you a picture.

217
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,400
Then when you get off work,

218
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,730
we can go home together.

219
00:16:20,410 --> 00:16:21,710
But...

220
00:16:22,910 --> 00:16:23,540
Alright.

221
00:16:24,410 --> 00:16:25,740
You're going to be late.

222
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,650
Go to work.

223
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:31,600
[Dalang: Korean Skewers,
Fried Chicken, Drinks]

224
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,640
This is my secret base.

225
00:16:43,380 --> 00:16:44,510
Secret base?

226
00:17:10,069 --> 00:17:13,690
[Dalang: Korean Skewers,
Fried Chicken, Drinks]

227
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:12,460
I'm leaving now.

228
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:13,230
Bye.

229
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:21,000
Why are you here?

230
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:22,440
I told you

231
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,170
I'd wait for you to get off work.

232
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:28,180
Is it

233
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,710
that serious?

234
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:33,330
The doctor said

235
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:35,080
I just need to keep it immobile for now.

236
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,450
A few days of rest and I'll be fine.

237
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:37,270
But

238
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:39,120
you're on the basketball team.

239
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,530
You still want to play
for the national team.

240
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:42,260
-How can you say...
-It's fine.

241
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:43,820
It's just a minor injury.

242
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:45,370
It's wrapped up like that,

243
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:47,770
and you're still calling it
a minor injury?

244
00:17:48,050 --> 00:17:50,960
[Dalang: Korean Skewers,
Fried Chicken, Drinks]

245
00:17:50,130 --> 00:17:50,800
I'll do it.

246
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:51,730
For the next few days,

247
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:52,970
you have to listen to me.

248
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:54,170
No pushing yourself.

249
00:17:55,270 --> 00:17:55,640
Okay.

250
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:56,890
I'll listen to you.

251
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:03,910
I'm just injured,

252
00:18:03,910 --> 00:18:05,010
not disabled.

253
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:08,310
If you're injured,
you need to take good care of yourself.

254
00:18:09,770 --> 00:18:10,900
Where are you going?

255
00:18:11,850 --> 00:18:13,710
I'm going to bring in the laundry.

256
00:18:15,510 --> 00:18:16,370
I'll do it.

257
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:17,220
Go sit down.

258
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:19,530
You really don't have to do this.

259
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:20,560
Go sit down.

260
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:22,430
Sit.

261
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:54,700
I won't take it.

262
00:18:58,820 --> 00:18:59,950
Where are you going?

263
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,460
I'm going to take a shower.

264
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:16,820
Are you okay?

265
00:19:16,820 --> 00:19:17,520
What's up?

266
00:19:17,650 --> 00:19:18,620
I'm fine.

267
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:21,430
[Basketball Tournament]

268
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:30,680
I'm sorry.

269
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:34,130
I caused you so much trouble.

270
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:36,570
You say

271
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:38,010
I'm always thanking you,

272
00:19:38,670 --> 00:19:40,070
but you're no different.

273
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:41,810
You're always apologizing to me.

274
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:43,340
But I'm really sorry.

275
00:19:44,010 --> 00:19:45,970
If I hadn't fallen just now,

276
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:46,650
I would...

277
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:47,850
If it weren't for me,

278
00:19:49,110 --> 00:19:50,840
you wouldn't have gotten hurt.

279
00:20:00,290 --> 00:20:02,320
I really don't want

280
00:20:02,730 --> 00:20:04,130
anyone else

281
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:06,960
to get hurt because of me again.

282
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:09,650
I know.

283
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,110
You're afraid of troubling others,

284
00:20:13,110 --> 00:20:15,440
and you're afraid of
becoming a burden to them.

285
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,500
So you carry everything by yourself.

286
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,500
But to me,

287
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:21,170
being someone you need

288
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:23,180
is something I'm lucky to be.

289
00:20:29,860 --> 00:20:31,190
Is that

290
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:33,490
so?

291
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:34,660
Yeah.

292
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:37,830
You've already done very well.

293
00:20:39,330 --> 00:20:40,230
Really?

294
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:46,560
I couldn't even protect

295
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:48,440
He's secret place.

296
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,150
How can I say I did a great job?

297
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:56,080
If you

298
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,470
really miss him,

299
00:20:58,450 --> 00:21:00,380
then let yourself think about him.

300
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,390
Don't rush to forget him.

301
00:21:10,260 --> 00:21:11,470
You're so good to me.

302
00:21:12,770 --> 00:21:13,570
Panda.

303
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:20,250
What's your name?

304
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,610
Everyone calls me Panda.

305
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,080
I'll go tidy up the room.

306
00:21:26,790 --> 00:21:27,920
Wait for me a moment.

307
00:22:03,130 --> 00:22:03,930
You found out?

308
00:22:22,610 --> 00:22:23,810
Do you remember this?

309
00:22:26,460 --> 00:22:27,260
Of course.

310
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,140
Didn't I give this to you?

311
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:31,770
I didn't expect you to keep it until now.

312
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:32,880
This is for you.

313
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:44,560
Back then,

314
00:22:45,260 --> 00:22:47,120
when I heard you were moving away,

315
00:23:16,590 --> 00:23:18,110
I chased after the car

316
00:23:18,130 --> 00:23:19,260
holding the panda doll

317
00:23:19,260 --> 00:23:20,720
for such a long, long time.

318
00:23:21,010 --> 00:23:23,070
And I cried for such a long, long time.

319
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,080
I'm sorry.

320
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:31,870
Something happened at home back then,

321
00:23:32,660 --> 00:23:35,120
and my aunt suddenly decided
we were moving.

322
00:23:36,340 --> 00:23:37,670
We didn't even have time

323
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:39,150
to say goodbye.

324
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:40,330
I never blamed you.

325
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,350
Actually,

326
00:23:42,540 --> 00:23:44,000
I was already really happy

327
00:23:44,620 --> 00:23:46,030
when I got to see you again

328
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,660
after school started.

329
00:23:49,790 --> 00:23:50,760
Hello, everyone.

330
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:51,830
I'm Junjia.

331
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,880
So you recognized me back then?

332
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:05,230
Then why didn't you tell me?

333
00:24:06,170 --> 00:24:07,770
We were still kids back then.

334
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,040
I was afraid I was the only one
who remembered

335
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,280
and that would've been embarrassing.

336
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,280
No way.

337
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:16,140
Besides, I remember you used to
cry all the time.

338
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:18,150
You were so chubby back then.

339
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:55,910
[Preview of the Next Episode]

340
00:26:53,670 --> 00:26:56,040
I really want to finish He's song.

341
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:58,980
It's just that

342
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:00,950
the more I sing this song,

343
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:02,280
the more it feels wrong.

344
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,380
Excuse me,

345
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,910
have you seen Zheng Diaoqin?

346
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,570
He went to the hospital
for a follow-up today.

347
00:27:12,180 --> 00:27:12,720
Junjia!

